  <description type="morphology">Stems decumbent to erect, 16–39 cm, moderately to densely strigose, sparsely to abundantly long-hirsute, eglandular or sparsely stipitate-glandular. Distal cauline leaf blades oblanceolate, 21–35 × 3.5–6 mm, bases narrowly cuneate to attenuate, margins flat, apices acute, faces moderately strigose (20–60 hairs/mm2), eglandular or sparsely stipitate-glandular. Heads 1–12(–25). Peduncles (5–)12–47(–67) mm, sparsely to densely hispido-strigose, eglandular; bracts subtending heads usually none, rarely linear-oblanceolate, leaflike. Involucres narrowly cylindric to campanulate (fresh), (5–)6–9(–11) mm. Phyllaries narrowly triangular-lanceolate, margins usually reddish purple distally, faces moderately to densely strigose, eglandular. Ray florets 10–27(–38), laminae (6.5–)8.5–15(–20) mm. 2n = 18, 36.</description>
